        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-11-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-11-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="456" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d456">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/11–1148: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-11-11">November 11,
                            1948</date>.<lb/>[Received November 11—4:44 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2174. Nanking Defense Command informs Military Attaché that martial law declared
                    at midnight November 10 in area bounded roughly by Hangchow, Shanghai, Pangfou
                        [<hi rend="italic">Pengpu?</hi>], Anking, Wuhu and Nanking. Nightly curfew
                    2300 hours to 0600 hours.</p>
                <p>Sent Department 2174; repeated Shanghai 1078.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
